   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">G</seg>OOD Reader, The trāslatour of the treatice of
<hi>Pa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tience</hi> lately printed, had also rendred this of
<hi>Benig<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>nity</hi> out of the same Au<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tour: but it came not in time to be dispatched with it; &amp; therefore goeth here a parte by it selfe. It will serue no lesse then that o<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ther <pb facs="3"/>of <hi>Patience</hi> to inamour vs with <hi>Christ</hi> our Lord, if we will consider the vn<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>speakable sweetnesse of his charity, whilest he made the world happy by con<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>uersing in it. The parti<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>culars whereof thou shalt finde, Good Reader, admi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>rably expressed in this trea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tice by this holy Autour; which is therefore recom<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mended vnto thee.</p>
</div>
